<td><span style="font-family: Verdana,Arial; font-size: 12px;"><p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Dear John,</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Please accept my sincere thanks for your support this
year. Although 2010 was a difficult year, we accomplished some of our key
legislative and electoral goals with your help. As 2010 comes to a close, I
want to say &ldquo;thank you&rdquo; again for your tremendous support and let you know what
we&rsquo;ll be working on next year.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">With your help this year, we were able to achieve several
significant environmental victories. We defeated the Murkowski resolution to
gut the Clean Air Act by six votes in the Senate. On Election Day, we defended
several critical allies and defeated seven of LCV&rsquo;s Dirty Dozen members &ndash;
including California&rsquo;s Prop 23, which would have suspended the state&rsquo;s landmark
climate legislation. We worked closely with state partners to defeat six members
of the first-ever state level Dirty Dozen. We truly could not have achieved
these wins without your support.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">It&rsquo;s no secret that the 112th Congress will be an
adverse environment for our agenda. The Senate will be closely divided and the
House will be controlled by climate deniers like Rep. John Boehner, who has an
abysmal LCV lifetime score of 2% and recently stated, <em>&ldquo;&hellip;the idea that carbon dioxide is a carcinogen that is harmful to our
environment is almost comical. Every time we exhale, we exhale carbon dioxide.
Every cow in the world, you know, when they do what they do, you&rsquo;ve got more
carbon dioxide</em>.&rdquo; So we&rsquo;re not kidding ourselves: We have a tough fight
ahead. That being said, <strong>we know we have
the opportunity for critical environmental gains with the Administration and
prevent major setbacks in Congress.</strong></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">While we don&rsquo;t expect to see comprehensive climate
legislation in Congress, LCV will work with the Obama administration to ensure
it uses its authority to take meaningful action to limit global warming
pollutants and build a clean energy economy.&nbsp;
Additionally, LCV will mount a vigorous campaign to defend against congressional
efforts to gut the Clean Air Act and prevent the EPA from holding corporate
polluters accountable.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">LCV will also work to strategically <strong>identify opportunities to reduce global warming pollution and make
progress on clean energy policies in key states</strong> whose governors or
legislatures are friendly to the environment. After the defeat of California&rsquo;s
Prop 23 in November, LCV plans to build on this success to strengthen state
emissions reduction legislation.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">A major campaign for LCV will be to <strong>hold the media accountable</strong> for distorting the truth about climate
science. There&rsquo;s no doubt that Glenn Beck, Rush Limbaugh, Sarah Palin and
others will continue their assault on the sound and settled science of climate
change. When they attempt to confuse and mislead the public about the dangers
of carbon pollution and our dependence on oil, LCV will respond aggressively &ndash;
mobilizing activists to respond to their lies and fight for the truth.</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">LCV will use several strategies to encourage pro-environment
policies, hold the media accountable, and defeat these threats:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Mobilize environmental activists to contact
their elected officials via phone, e-mail and in-person prior to key votes</span></li>
<li style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Publish the <em>National
Environmental Scorecard</em>, the most respected yardstick for measuring
political leaders&rsquo; environmental records and holding them accountable</span></li>
<li style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Utilize new online organizing tactics, including
various social media tools, to recruit and engage a new generation of clean
energy advocates and ambassadors</span></li>
<li style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Educate
     voters about the benefits of creating a clean energy economy to build
     pressure for progress in the states, and from there to the national level</span></li>
<li style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Coordinate
     with our state LCV partners and other key allies to build a broad and
     diverse network of supporters in key states</span></li>
</ul>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">We know that these strategies work, but they take
significant resources to execute. We have our work cut out for us in 2011 and
we cannot do it alone. <a title="C4 2010 Year End Campaign" href="http://action.lcv.org/site/R?i=UluoatINV-b-wV4IzfEGfA.."><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Will you
please consider making an end-of-year contribution today that will allow us to
hit the ground running in 2011?</span></strong></a></span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Thank you for your continued support of LCV&rsquo;s work. </span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;">Sincerely,</span></p>
<p style="margin: 0em 0em 1em; text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #000000;"><img src="http://action.lcv.org/images/content/pagebuilder/11528.gif" border="0" alt="Gene_only_sig_web.gif" width="86" height="65" /><br />Gene Karpinski<br />President<br />League of Conservation Voters</span></p><img src="http://action.lcv.org/site/PixelServer?j=j96puPsVNzs8Uqz5RMG5Pw.." height="1" width="1">
